{"id":3059,"date":"2012-04-26T08:58:01","date_gmt":"2012-04-26T12:58:01","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=3059"},"modified":"2024-01-03T10:17:08","modified_gmt":"2024-01-03T06:17:08","slug":"no-gift-better-than-sabr","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/26\/no-gift-better-than-sabr\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Sabr: No gift better than patience, resilience"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: Some people from the Ansar asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he gave them. Then they asked for charity again and he gave them. Then they asked again and he gave them until all he had was gone. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>If I had anything, I would not withhold it. Whoever refrains from asking others, then Allah will make him content. Whoever would be independent, then Allah will make him <strong>independent<\/strong>. Whoever seeks to be patient, then Allah will make him patient. No one is given a gift that is better and more comprehensive than patience<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6470, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1053<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/strong><\/em> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064b\u0627 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650 \u0633\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u06